						<summary>

						<p>Kshaya = c. 14th-15th Century.</p>						

						<p>This says that the temple trustees of Aḻimbil-nayiṉār and the ten <hi rend="italic">perumpar (?)</hi> decided that the stone (or wooden pole) planted to mark the <hi rend="italic">chēttaḷavu</hi> (probably the height of water level) should not be removed for ever. A low-relief sculpture of Liṅga as protected by a cow is just below the inscription.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 975.]</p>						

						</summary>
